title: Euri Lighting EMP-2000cec-15, Dimmable LED Light Engine, 5.12" Diameter, 15W (100W Equal), 1350lm, 3000K, 4000K, 5000K, 90+ CRI, Energy Star, CEC Compliant, 5YR, 50K Hour WTY
description:
Introducing the EMP-2000cec-15 LED Light Engine from Euri Lighting, the perfect solution for upgrading your existing light fixtures to energy-efficient LED technology. This high-quality LED module boasts a seamless light output and hassle-free installation, making it the ideal retrofit option for incandescent, fluorescent, or LED-integrated fixtures. With its tool-less installation process, retrofitting your light fixtures with this LED module is as simple as screwing in a light bulb. By eliminating the need to replace existing LED fixtures, you can reduce unsightly hot spots and enjoy optimal light output. Euri Lighting recommends retrofitting fixtures 4” or less in diameter for the best results. The EMP-2000cec-15 LED Light Engine features a wattage of 15W and a selectable color temperature ranging from 3000K to 5000K. It also boasts a high color rendering index (CRI) of 90+, ensuring that colors appear vibrant and true-to-life. With its dimmable function using Triac, you can easily adjust the light output to create the perfect ambiance. This LED module is damp rated, making it ideal for use in damp environments such as bathrooms and kitchens. Its beam angle of 110 degrees ensures a wide spread of light, providing ample illumination for any space. The estimated lifespan of the lamp is an impressive 50,000 hours, and the yearly cost is estimated to be a mere $1.80. With its mechanical dimensions of 5.12" in diameter and 1.22" in height, this LED module is compact and easy to install. It has an operational temperature range of 13°F to 113°F, making it suitable for use in a wide range of environments.
Easy Installation
Step 1. Cut off the power supply.
Step 2. Disassemble the lampshade of the lamp that needs to be modified.
Step 3. Remove the light source, ballast and other accessories of the original lamp.
Step 4. Connect wires, white to white, black to black.
Step 5. Slide the light engine center through the lamp pole screw. Stick the light engine to the backplate of the Fixture (the light engine screws are magnetic).
Step 6. Reassemble the lampshade to complete installation.
features: [Instant Savings] See an immediate decline on your next electricity bill once you switch over to Euri's MPLRs. With an 84% decrease in energy consumption from incandescent bulbs and an estimated energy cost of $1. 92 per year, your wallet will thank you!

[Keep the Style You Love] Why throw away your existing decorative fixtures when you can keep the same look and upgrade to LED technology? Simple hard wiring for a hassle free and easy installation. This LED module can be mounted with center threaded screw type fixture, or directly to flat fixture bases with mounting screws. Euri MPLRs also be used to replace compact fluorescent lamps or fluorescent circline lamps. (Ballast bypass required for circline)

[Triac Dimming] Dim to 10% from full illumination with triac dimming capacities. Get rid of ugly hotspots in your fixture and have uniform light distribution with Euri Lightings MPLR Retrofit Kit. This LED light engine is designed to have excellent light quality (90+ Color Rendering Index) and a high lumen output with minimal energy consumption.

[Multi Purpose LED Retrofit] This LED Light Engine has many different applications is can be used for as it's very versatile: Flush Mount Ceiling Fixture, Pendant Fixture, Portable Lamp Fixture, Floor Lamps (E26 adapter sold separately), and Ceiling Fan Lights.

[Longer Lifespan] Euri's MPLR fixtures come with an extensive 5 Year and a 50,000 Hour Lifespan. Built to last and carrying the lighting industries highest accolades, this fixture carries ETL, Energy Star, and CEC (California Energy Commission) Certifications.
